==Korean==
===Noun===
'''개''' (''gae'')
# [[dog]] (''cf. Middle English [[dogge]], Old English [[docga]], probably from '''docile''' + '''ga''''')
# [[estuary]]

====Alternative spellings====
* [[긔]] (''gui'') (''obsolete; unauthorized'') cf. Breton [[ki]],  Welsh [[ci]] 
* [[가히]] (''gahi'') (''obsolete'')

====Synonyms====
*[[견]] ([[犬]], ''gyeon'') [[dog]]  cf. [[hound]], [[hunt]], German [[Hund]], Frisian [[hûn]], Albanian [[qen]], Ladin [[cian]], French [[chien]], Provençal [[can]],  Italian [[cane]],  Latin [[canis]] 
*[[구]] ([[狗]], ''gu'') [[dog]] cf. Irish [[cú]], Scottish Gaelic [[cù]]

====Derived terms====
* 개[[새끼]] (''-saekki'') [[puppy]]; [[son of a bitch]]
* [[들]]개 (''deul-'') [[wild]] dog  
* [[사냥]]개 (''sanyang-'') [[hunter]], [[hound]] cf. German [[Hund]] "dog" (''cognate with Latin [[canis]]'')
* [[수캐]] (''sukae'') [[male]] [[dog]]
* [[암캐]] (''amkae'') [[female]] [[dog]], [[bitch]]

====See also====
* [[견유]] (gyeon-yu) [[cynic]]
* [[길들이다]] (''gildeurIda'') To [[domesticate]], [[tame]], [[train]], (''cf. Latin [[docere]] "to teach"'')
* [[순하다]] ([[順]]-, ''sun-hada'') To be [[mild]], [[docile]] (''from Latin [[docere]] "to teach"''), cf. Old Prussian [[sunis]] "dog"

